Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{1%sachet},
then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Apple & Walnut Salad ==

In the meantime, quarter, core, and finely chop the @apple{1}(quartered and
finely chopped, no need to peel).

Roughly chop the @walnuts{20%grams}.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Toss the apple through the dressing and set aside for later.

== Cheesy Rosemary Chips ==

When turning the chips halfway through cooking, sprinkle over the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}.

When the chips have about 10 mins left, place the
@unconventional plant-based burgers{2} on a lightly oiled baking tray and bake
on the middle shelf until browned, ~{8-9%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

== Burger Assembly ==

When there's 5 mins of cooking time left, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop them
onto the #burger tray{} in the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, toss the walnuts and half the @wild rocket{40%grams}(half) through
the dressed apple.

When everything's ready, spread the @goat's cheese{75%grams} over the cooked
burgers.

Spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun bases, add a handful of the
remaining wild rocket and top with the goat's cheese burgers. Spread the
@fig jam{40%grams} over the bun lids and sandwich shut.

Serve with the cheesy chips and apple and walnut salad alongside.

Enjoy!